    <item>
      <title>Git</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/git/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Mar 2026 14:54:56 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/git/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The first thing I do when starting a new project is initialize Git and create a repository on Github, Gitlab, or Codeberg.&#xA;No matter the size of your project, even if it&amp;rsquo;s just a couple of code files for an experiment and you&amp;rsquo;re the only one working on it, I recommend doing it in a version control system.&#xA;Git allows you to add new lines and remove old lines without worrying about losing anything valuable in your files. You can view the change history and revert to a previous version at any time.&#xA;If you haven&amp;rsquo;t used it yet, there&amp;rsquo;s a great &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/git-guides/&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;guide&lt;/a&gt; that will introduce you to the basic commands and get you up to speed on workflows. Every project of mine starts with these commands in the console:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Start CI process</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/start-ci-process/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 21 Jan 2026 14:04:24 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/notes/start-ci-process/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;And again about CI.&#xA;Imagine you need to run a CI process, but you haven&amp;rsquo;t made any changes to the code and there&amp;rsquo;s no manual process launch option for this CI.&#xA;You have two options:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Rewrite the hash of the last commit and force push:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git commit --amend --no-edit --allow-empty&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git push -f&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Add a new empty commit and do a regular push:&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git commit --allow-empty -m &amp;#39;Run CI&amp;#39;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git push&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Which option is more acceptable for you?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to continue using a repository after cloning</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-continue-using-repo-after-cloning/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 02 Nov 2025 22:25:00 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-continue-using-repo-after-cloning/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes you just clone a repository to experiment with the project&amp;rsquo;s code and don&amp;rsquo;t know in advance whether you&amp;rsquo;ll be sending pull requests.&#xA;You do:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git clone git@github.com:user/project.git&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;cd project&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# and try to compile or run code&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then, at some point, when you find a bug or just want to add new functionality, you fork the repository on GitHub. And instead of cloning your newly created fork into a new folder and manually transferring your changes, you can run these commands and continue working in the same folder you cloned the original repository into:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How localy merge Github Pull Request</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-localy-merge-github-pull-request/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 10:05:42 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-localy-merge-github-pull-request/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Follow this commands for merge PR with favors the foreign merging tree in conflict resolution:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;PR=25&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;USER_BRANCH=&amp;#39;username:branch&amp;#39;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git checkout master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git pull origin master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git fetch origin pull/$PR/head:$PR&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git merge -X theirs $PR -m &amp;#39;Merge pull request #&amp;#39;&amp;#34;$PR&amp;#34;&amp;#39; from &amp;#39;&amp;#34;$USER_BRANCH&amp;#34;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git push origin master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git branch $PR -d&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How add commits to Pull Request on Github</title>
      <link>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-add-commits-to-pr-on-github/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2025 11:40:20 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yegorov.github.io/posts/how-add-commits-to-pr-on-github/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes there are situations when you need to add your commits to the PR that was sent to your repository.&#xA;Follow these commands (taken from &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/reviewing-changes-in-pull-requests/checking-out-pull-requests-locally&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;), but first of all, make sure that the PR author set checkbox &amp;ldquo;Allow edits by maintainers&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Update you main repository&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git checkout master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git pull origin master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Fetch PR 19 to local branch 19&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git fetch origin pull/19/head:19&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Move to PR branch&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git checkout 19&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Make some change&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git show HEAD&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git commit -m &amp;#34;Add some commit info&amp;#34;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Add remote fork repository&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git remote -v&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git remote add username git@github.com:username/reponame.git&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Push my local branch to branch in fork repository&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git push username 19:patch-1&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Pull new commits&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git checkout master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git pull origin master&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Delete local branch&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git branch 19 -d&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;# Remove origin&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;git remote remove username&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
